{"title_page": "Game.EXE", "text_new": "{{Underlinked|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox magazine\n|title=Game.EXE\n|image_file=Game.EXE_magazine_April_2005_front_cover.jpg\n|image_size=\n|image_caption=\n|editor=\u0418\u0433\u043e\u0440\u044c \u0418\u0441\u0443\u043f\u043e\u0432\n|editor_title=Chief editor\n|frequency=1995 \u2013 bi-monthly<br/>1996\u20132006 \u2013 monthly\n|circulation=\n|publisher=\u041a\u043e\u043c\u043f\u044c\u044e\u0442\u0435\u0440\u0440\u0430 (Computerra)<!--There is a Computerra article, but it's about another magazine-->\n|category=Video games\n|founder=\n|company=\n|firstdate=March 1995\n|finaldate=June 2006\n|finalnumber=134\n|country=Russia\n|language=[[Russian language|Russian]]\n|issn=1819-2734\n|website=http://www.game-exe.ru/\n}}\n\n'''''Game.EXE''''' is a now-defunct monthly Russian magazine focused on [[video games]]. It was initially launched titled ''Toy Shop'' ({{lang-ru|\u041c\u0430\u0433\u0430\u0437\u0438\u043d \u0438\u0433\u0440\u0443\u0448\u0435\u043a}}) from March 1995 to December 1996. Starting 1997, it was renamed ''Game.EXE'' and ran until June 2006, with the last 4 issues all published in June.\n\n== References ==\n* {{cite web |url=http://exe-community.com.ru/modules/news/article.php?storyid=436 |title=\u0418\u043d\u0442\u0435\u0440\u0432\u044c\u044e \u0441\u043e\u043e\u0431\u0449\u0435\u0441\u0442\u0432\u0430 \u0441 \"\u043c\u043e\u0433\u0443\u0447\u0435\u0439 \u043a\u0443\u0447\u043a\u043e\u0439\" \u043a\u043e\u043b\u043b\u0435\u043a\u0442\u0438\u0432\u0430 Game.EXE |trans-title=Interview with the \"might pack\" of Game.EXE collective |first1=\u041c\u0438\u0445\u0430\u0438\u043b |last1=\u0410\u043b\u0435\u043a\u0441\u0430\u043d\u0434\u0440\u043e\u0432 |first2=\u0410\u0440\u0441\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0439 |last2=\u0421\u043e\u043a\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0432 |date=2013-02-09 |publisher=Game.EXE reader community |access-date=2013-03-05 |language=Russian |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150610221540/http://exe-community.com.ru/modules/news/article.php?storyid=436 |archive-date=10 June 2015 |url-status=dead |df= }}\n* {{cite web |url=http://kanobu.ru/articles/intervyu-igor-isupov-362831/ |script-title=ru:\u0418\u043d\u0442\u0435\u0440\u0432\u044c\u044e. \u0418\u0433\u043e\u0440\u044c \u0418\u0441\u0443\u043f\u043e\u0432 |trans-title=Interview. Igor Ispupov |first1=\u0412\u043b\u0430\u0434\u0438\u043c\u0438\u0440 |last1=\u0420\u044b\u0436\u043a\u043e\u0432 |first2=\u0412\u0438\u043a\u0442\u043e\u0440 |last2=\u0417\u0443\u0435\u0432 |date=1 February 2013 |publisher=Kanobu.ru |access-date=2013-03-05 |language=Russian |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6EzP1SPBX?url=http://kanobu.ru/articles/intervyu-igor-isupov-362831/ |archive-date=2013-03-09 |url-status=live |df= }}\n* {{cite web |url=http://kanobu.ru/videos/teoriia-igr/teoriya-igr-gameexe-chast-1-363880/ |title=\u0422\u0435\u043e\u0440\u0438\u044f \u0418\u0433\u0440. Game.EXE. \u0427\u0430\u0441\u0442\u044c 1 |trans-title=Game Theory. Game.EXE. Part 1 |first=\u0412\u044f\u0447\u0435\u0441\u043b\u0430\u0432 |last=\u041c\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0438\u0446\u043a\u0438\u0439 |date=11 February 2013 |publisher=Kanobu.ru |access-date=2013-03-05 |language=Russian |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6EzP4shTw?url=http://kanobu.ru/videos/teoriia-igr/teoriya-igr-gameexe-chast-1-363880/ |archive-date=2013-03-09 |url-status=live |df= }}\n* {{cite web |url=http://kanobu.ru/videos/teoriia-igr/teoriya-igr-gameexe-chast-2-364228/ |title=\u0422\u0435\u043e\u0440\u0438\u044f \u0418\u0433\u0440. Game.EXE. \u0427\u0430\u0441\u0442\u044c 2 |trans-title=Game Theory. Game.EXE. Part 2 |first=\u0412\u044f\u0447\u0435\u0441\u043b\u0430\u0432 |last=\u041c\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0438\u0446\u043a\u0438\u0439 |date=15 February 2013 |publisher=Kanobu.ru |access-date=2013-03-05 |language=Russian |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6EzP7J8w7?url=http://kanobu.ru/videos/teoriia-igr/teoriya-igr-gameexe-chast-2-364228/ |archive-date=2013-03-09 |url-status=live |d